HEADWORD: Catacaustic
<hw>Cat`a*caus"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>cata + caustic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Relating to,
or having the properties of, a caustic curve formed by reflection. See
<er>Caustic</er>, <pos>a.</pos></def> <rj><au>Nichol.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catacaustic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Catacaustic
<hw>Cat`a*caus"tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A
caustic curve formed by reflection of light.</def>
<rj><au>Nichol.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

